cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "Fine-tuning Qwen2.5-7B for Frequent Itemset Extraction: An Apriori-Oracle Approach"
authors:
  - family-names: Slivka
    given-names: Oliver
    affiliation: "Faculty of Informatics and Statistics, Prague University of Economics and Business (FIS VŠE Praha)"
    orcid: ""
type: software
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-04-XX"
repository-code: "https://github.com/OliverSlivka/itemsety-qwen-finetuning"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  An end-to-end ML pipeline for fine-tuning Qwen2.5-7B to extract frequent
  itemsets from transactional CSV data. Uses the Apriori algorithm as a
  deterministic ground-truth oracle, eliminating the need for human annotation.
  Training strategy: Supervised Fine-Tuning with Chain-of-Thought reasoning
  (348 examples) followed by Direct Preference Optimization on real LLM
  failure pairs (606 examples). Evaluated on a held-out set of 30 synthetic
  datasets. SFT+DPO achieves F1=11.8%; GPT-4.1-mini baseline achieves
  F1=49.1%. Developed as part of a bachelor's thesis at FIS VŠE Praha (2026).
keywords:
  - machine-learning
  - fine-tuning
  - frequent-itemset-mining
  - lora
  - dpo
  - qwen
  - nlp
  - apriori
  - unstructured-to-structured
